id: shape/orientation-shape
title: "orientation shape"
kind: shape-primitive
status: v0-seed
updated: 2026-07-03

definition: >
  An orientation shape is the structured frame that makes part of an
  information field inspectable before action.

path:
  - field
  - orientation
  - inference
  - lacuna
  - boundary
  - move
  - proof
  - memory

stable_claim: >
  Any observing agent lives inside an information field it cannot fully hold.
  .yawn gives that agent a shape for orienting: what was noticed, what was
  inferred, what is missing, what is bounded, what can move, what proved
  change, and what memory updates.

why_shape: >
  Shape is the readable capsule. A human can inspect it, an LLM can read it, a
  repo can version it, a bot can compare it, and a proof receipt can update it.

boundary:
  - "Shape does not mean reality is literally code."
  - "Shape means a structured frame for making partial information inspectable."
  - "Only proof updates the map."

proof:
  source:
    - readme.yawn
    - templates/orientation-shape.yawn
  status: seed-backed
